"{\n  \"text\": \"Hi everybody, I'm here in Neadville, Texas, and we are going to be doing a regenerative agriculture project here. It's a 14-acre plot, and we are going to try to regenerate one of the acres for the spring crop. Um it's now November, so hopefully by April we'll have enough compost to do one acre of this 14-acre plot. We're going to set it into probably 20, 50 foot long rows, and then use wood chips, which you'll see the giant pile over here, to creep uh a mulch and a weed control. One of the big things about regenerative agriculture is using wood chips to control your weeds. This is uh much better than plowing and tilling and implying poisons because this creates uh a better soil in the long run for you. These will break down and actually become a soil amendment as opposed to the poisons, which are just going to kill your microbes. Anyway, thanks, y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hi everybody, I'm here in Neadville, Texas, and we are going to be doing a regenerative agriculture project here.\",\n      \"start\": 1.28,\n      \"end\": 7.2,\n      \"duration\": 5.92,\n      \"confidence\": 0.995,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" Hi\",\n          \"start\": 1.28,\n          \"end\": 1.6,\n          \"duration\": 0.32,\n          \"confidence\": 0.992\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 1.76,\n          \"end\": 1.84,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 1.84,\n          \"end\": 2.0,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ody\",\n          \"start\": 2.0,\n          \"end\": 2.08,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \",\",\n          \"start\": 2.08,\n          \"end\": 2.16,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\":